title: Inelastic scattering of heavy ions.

x4freetext: Inelastic scattering of heavy ions.

x4codes.hlp: Yale University, New Haven, CT, United States of America

x4freetext: Heavy ion accelerator.
The RCA solid state detector and an RIDL 400-
channel analyser. The experimentally observed
resolution of the detector system was from 1% to 2%.
The target gas was flowed continuously through the
scattering volume. The pressure was maintained constant
with a manostat.
Pressure and ambient temperature readings were
regularly made and were used to correct the yield at
each angle. These corrections in no case amounted to
more than 1%.
Pressure-temperature corrections and dead time
corrections were then applied to the data. In the worst
cases the dead time corrections amounted to as much as
10%. The probable error due to this effect has been
estimated as +-3%, assuming an uncertainty of 30% in
these corrections. The geometric corrections were in
all cases less than 0.3%.
The counting statistics varied from point to point,
depending upon the angle being taken and the time
available. Typical values are from 3% to 9%.
Energy determination accuracy was better than 2%.

from double excitation of the 4.433 MeV level,
excitation of the 9.63 level or nucleon exchange
collisions.
